This paper deals with image search and watermark detection, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) and information retrieval (cs.IR) categories. The use of deep convolutional neural networks (CNNs) also suggests the machine learning (cs.LG) category. Additionally, the paper discusses the design of a new metric, which could fall under the multimedia (cs.MM) category. Finally, the paper mentions the analysis of images based on their domains, which could fall under the cryptography and security (cs.CR) category.
